"We are devastated about the recent cancer diagnosis of our older son Noah, who is currently undergoing treatment in the US," Bubl and his Argentinian actress wife, Luisana Lopilato, wrote on his Facebook page on Friday."Luisana and I have put our careers on hold in order to devote all our time and attention to helping Noah get well," the couple said.Bubl did not say what kind of cancer his son is suffering from, but hoped the family "will win this battle". Noah is the first child of the couple, who married in 2011.Their second son was born in January.Bubl , 41, has carved out an international career and won four Grammy awards with easy listening pop songs like his 2009 hit Haven't Met You Yet.